        "content": "<p>Hi, I'm not sure, but I found a clue</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">namespace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Clue</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- set_option autoImplicit false</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">bs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">--                     ^^ removing the `as` fixes it?</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">append_assoc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">++</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">++</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">++</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">++</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cs</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rcases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">as</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">repeat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">nil_append</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">repeat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cons_append</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">congrArg</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">append_assoc</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">append_assoc</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">end</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Clue</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Maybe supplying <code>as</code> in the variable declarations interferes with the type inference somehow?</p>",
