        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>For better or for worse, the interaction of <code>variable</code> and recursion is that the arguments in <code>variable</code> are fixed throughout the recursion. So there is a semantic difference, and the not working proof would indeed not work.</p>\n<p>But the error message is certainly not the right one here.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>From issue <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/issues/8282#issuecomment-2869529772\">comment</a> by <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"470149\">@Joachim Breitner</span>.</p>\n<p>I'm copying it here so that the topic doesn't seem obtuse to be marked as resolved.</p>",
